---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";

const timeline = [
    { time: "Hour 1-3", action: "Avoid eating until numbness is 100% gone." },
    {
        time: "Day 1-3",
        action: "Mild sensitivity is normal. Use Ibuprofen as directed.",
    },
    {
        time: "Week 1-4",
        action: "Return for your permanent Crown (VERY IMPORTANT).",
    },
];
---

<Layout title="Root Canal Recovery - Comfy Dental">
    <section class="bg-sand py-20">
        <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
            <div class="mb-12">
                <a
                    href="/patient-hub"
                    class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-primary font-bold mb-8 hover:-translate-x-1 transition-transform"
                >
                    <svg
                        class="w-5 h-5"
                        fill="none"
                        viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                        stroke="currentColor"
                        ><path
                            stroke-linecap="round"
                            stroke-linejoin="round"
                            stroke-width="2"
                            d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7"></path></svg
                    >
                    Back to Hub
                </a>
                <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold text-slate-800 mb-6">
                    Root Canal <span class="text-mocha">Recovery</span>
                </h1>
                <p class="text-xl text-slate-600 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
                    The hard part is over! Now, let's ensure your tooth stays
                    protected and pain-free during the final healing stage.
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- The Critical Warning -->
            <div
                class="bg-red-50 border-l-8 border-red-500 p-8 rounded-3xl mb-16 shadow-lg shadow-red-500/5"
            >
                <h3
                    class="text-xl font-bold text-red-800 mb-2 flex items-center gap-2"
                >
                    ⚠️ The #1 Rule for Success
                </h3>
                <p class="text-red-700 font-medium">
                    Do not chew or bite on the treated tooth until your
                    permanent crown is placed. The temporary filling is fragile
                    and the tooth can fracture if too much pressure is applied.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 mb-20">
                {
                    timeline.map((item) => (
                        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-[2.5rem] border border-slate-100 shadow-xl shadow-slate-200/50">
                            <p class="text-primary font-black uppercase text-xs tracking-widest mb-3">
                                {item.time}
                            </p>
                            <p class="text-slate-700 font-medium leading-relaxed">
                                {item.action}
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    ))
                }
            </div>

            <!-- FAQ Section specific to RCT -->
            <div class="space-y-6 mb-20">
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-800 mb-8">
                    Common Questions
                </h2>
                <div
                    class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border border-slate-100 shadow-sm"
                >
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-800 mb-2">
                        Can I brush the tooth?
                    </h4>
                    <p class="text-slate-600">
                        Yes, keep the area clean. Brush and floss gently like
                        any other tooth, but be careful not to "pop" out the
                        temporary filling with floss.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div
                    class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border border-slate-100 shadow-sm"
                >
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-800 mb-2">
                        My jaw feels sore. Is that normal?
                    </h4>
                    <p class="text-slate-600">
                        Yes. Soreness in the jaw muscles is normal from keeping
                        your mouth open during the procedure. This will subside
                        in 2-3 days.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div
                    class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border border-slate-100 shadow-sm"
                >
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-800 mb-2">
                        What if the filling falls out?
                    </h4>
                    <p class="text-slate-600">
                        Temporary fillings are meant to be removed later. If it
                        chips a little, it's fine. If the whole thing falls out,
                        call us to have it replaced to prevent infection.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Call to Action -->
            <div
                class="bg-slate-900 rounded-[3rem] p-12 text-center text-white"
            >
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">
                    Ready for your Permanent Crown?
                </h3>
                <p class="text-slate-400 mb-8">
                    A root canal is not truly finished until the crown is
                    placed. Book your final appointment now.
                </p>
                <a
                    href="/contact"
                    class="inline-block px-10 py-4 bg-primary text-white font-bold rounded-2xl shadow-lg hover:scale-105 transition-transform"
                    >Book Restoration</a
                >
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</Layout>
